HEADWORD: Petworth marble
<hw>Pet"worth mar"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A kind of shell marble
occurring in the Wealden clay at Petworth, in Sussex, England; -- called
also <altname>Sussex marble</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petzite</ent>⟦br⟧
